Title: AILA Cosmetics Coconut Oil & Cuticle Therapy
Description: Our 100% Natural and Organic Coconut Oil cleans, hydrates, and strengthens nails & cuticles. It also performs as a powerful anti-oxidant, offering effective anti-aging protection. Our coconut oil has been extracted using an innovative extraction process that allows for greater preservation of lauric acid than normal cold-pressed techniques. While most coconut oils test within the range of 46-49 percent lauric acid content, ours contains 57% with an additional 70% content of medium chain fatty acids. The high levels of lauric acid in addition to caprylic and capric acids within coconut oil allows for greater anti-microbial and anti-fungal performance aiding in the prevention of bacterial growthin nails as well as providing luxurious hydration. The combination of these naturally occurring acids gently nourish and sooth nails and cuticles. *It's a fact: coconut oil melts at 74 degrees. During warm weather months, we recommend expedited shipping to prevent melting. Do not be alarmed if melting occurs. The oil will reconstitute and can be used as recommended.

Title: Rejsol Yellow Peel 50 ml with Neutralizer(50 ml)
Description: Glycolic Acid & Lactic Acid is Peeling agent that removes the superficial Dead skin layer and causes growth of new lighter glowing skin.Kojic Acid acts in decreasing the melanin therefore is very good de-pigmentation agent thus causes whiteningLactic ACID is derived from milk hence the name milk peel Retinol is Vitamin A and is a good whitening AgentChemical Peels are acids therefore should be used under the Supervision of trained cosmetologists.Always do Patch Test when using the peel for the first time.Patch test: Apply small amount of peel below neck or armpit, see for any redness beyond the margin of application, if seendiscontinue the procedure. If no redness or itching continue with the procedureProcedure:Cleanse the skin with oil free cleanser, if using oil containing cleanser, after cleansing whip with alcohol or spirit. oil blocks the acid therefore desired action is not achieved.Apply Peel with brush or ear Buds, gel peels can be best applied with gloved fingers. start applying from the forehead upto the neck, application time should not be more than 20 seconds. keep peel for 3-7 mins depending on your skin habituality of peeling and the peel strength. Spray neutralizer, keep for 1 min.wash with water., apply sunscreen and good moisturiser for 7 days twice daily.Post Peel:Success of the peeling depends on sunprotection and moisturisingfirst the skin dies so becomes black don't worry this is the skin that is going to peel of itselfThere are two types of peeling microscopic that is not seen by naked eyes, and macroscopic peeling that is visualised very wellDo not remove the skin by your self.Don't use soap for 2-3 days, thereafter, use mild soap for 7-8 days, don't scrub too hardNote: If you don't get desired results doesnt mean the peel is not working it only means that your skin is tough for the peel you are using. then its time to use stronger peels or increase the application time of the peel in the next sitting.
